# Portfolio Website Implementation Plan

This document outlines the architecture, design, and implementation approach for building a world-class portfolio website for Sarvesh Kumar S S.

## Goal Description
Build a highly professional, modern, and dark-themed portfolio website tailored for top-tier software engineering roles (Backend & AI Systems). The website will emphasize scalability, reliability, and machine learning expertise, featuring a sleek, minimal design with smooth animations.

## Target Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js (App Router)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS
- **Animations**: Framer Motion
- **Icons**: Lucide React
- **Hosting**: Vercel (Target)

## Proposed Architecture & Components

### 1. Global Setup & Theming
- **Tailwind Configuration**: Deep dark color palette (blacks, deep blues, slate accents), modern typography (Inter or similar Google Font), custom utility classes for gradients and glassmorphism.
- **Background**: Implementation of a subtle, interactive particle or neural-network-like background using canvas or SVG.

### 2. UI Components
- **Navbar**: Sticky, glassmorphic header for smooth page navigation.
- **Section Container**: Reusable wrapper with Framer Motion scroll animations (fade in, slide up).
- **Cards**: Minimal, glowing or bordered cards for Projects and Experiences with subtle hover effects.
- **Buttons**: Premium call-to-action buttons (gradient backgrounds or sleek outlines).

### 3. Page Sections
- **Hero**: High-impact introduction with name, roles, tagline, and call-to-actions.
- **About Me**: Concise professional summary.
- **Technical Skills**: A structured visual grid grouping categorized skills.
- **Featured Projects**: Detailed project cards with tech stack tags, architecture descriptions, links, and animated elements.
- **Experience**: Timeline-based or card-based internship history.
- **Achievements & Certifications**: Grid or list highlighting awards and credentials.
- **Leadership**: Summary of executive and treasurer roles.
- **Contact**: Clean links to Email, GitHub, and LinkedIn.
- **Footer**: Custom engineered tagline.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> Please review this plan. If you are satisfied with the chosen stack (Next.js + Tailwind + Framer Motion) and the overall structure, please approve, and I will begin the project initialization and development.
